15/02/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government on Tuesday (14 February) announced plans to build the country's first nuclear reactor at Sinop on the Black Sea coast.
Officials said that such factors as geological fault lines and the availability of cooling water were taken into account when choosing the site.
In other news, a new study by the state statistical institute TurkStat finds that one out of four people in Turkey live below the poverty line.
The information is based on a household survey conducted in 2004.(TurkishPress.com, AP, Reuters, AFP, NTV - 14/02/06)
